</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p><strong>Stylish Work Outfits That Are Spring Trend Appropriate</strong></p>
<p>From the latest <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/best-designer-denim-collaborations/" target="_blank">designer denim collaborations</a> to <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/rachel-zoe-style-how-wear-sequins/" target="_blank">how to wear sequins for day</a>, our focus lately has been on updating your off-duty outfits so they are on trend. But your weekend wardrobe isn’t the only thing that should get a spring update. What to wear to work can be easily revamped by incorporating a few of the most versatile <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/womens-spring-summer-2013-trend-report/" target="_blank">spring trends</a>.</p>
<p>The runways had plenty of office-appropriate <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/fall-2013-fashion-week-best-street-style-trends/" target="_blank">inspiration</a> for stylish work outfits. Take the colored suit. No one said the one you wear to the office has to be black. Whether you wear the colored suit as one piece or mix up the pants and blazer as separates, it looks far fresher than the traditional one you’ve been wearing.</p>
<p>You can easily do the same with your pencil skirt. Because it’s a classic style, you can experiment with a <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/celebrity-stylist-jeanann-williams-how-wear-prints/">print</a>, keeping the rest of your pieces understated. And it’s a piece you can wear after work and on the weekend, too. (<a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/printed-skirt-2013-fashion-trends/" target="_blank">We show you how here</a>.)</p>
<p>When it comes to accessories, <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/fashion/how-wear-white-shoes/" target="_blank">the white pump</a> is a go-with-everything style that feels chic while still office-appropriate. And <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/shoes-bags/spring-bags-2013-new-bag-shape/" target="_blank">the mini bag</a> is the perfect way to retain the structured style of a <a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/woman/shoes-bags/structured-totes/" target="_blank">work tote</a> in a cooler size. Let’s be honest, you can edit down what you carry in there anyway.</p>
<p>Click through to shop the pieces you need for your stylish work outfits this spring. —<a href="http://www.lifestylemirror.com/search_content/?search_block_form=megan+hayes&amp;op=Search&amp;default_text=" target="_blank"><em>Megan Hayes</em></a><em> (</em><a href="https://twitter.com/_mshayes" target="_blank"><em>@_mshayes</em></a><em>)</em></p>
</div></div></div><div id="addthis-buttons" class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style">
